args:
Nedrick and his group meet King Jinlorda of the
Faerie Kingdom at the base of the Sacred Tree.
Using a secret art to maintain his body size,
the strengthened king now seeks to advance
his agenda in the outside worldâ€”but first offers
the truth of the prince and Nedrick's births.
North of the Faerie Kingdom\nThe Sacred Tree
How long do you intend to wait, Nedrick?
Should we not ascend the Sacred Tree?
The inside of the Sacred Tree is protected\nby all manner of faerie magics.
We await someone with the ability\nto undo those protections.
Cease your incessant questioning.\nYou will see in time.
Oh, Nedrick. You haven't changed a whit.
Found your way here at last, did you, Jin?
I see you still haven't taken my lessons\nabout treating women with kindness and\nrespect to heart.
And such rudeness to your own sister,\nno less! It truly is a sad state of affairs.
Forgive me, but who are you?
Permit me to offer my greetings, Auspex.\nAnd to you as well, Fourth Heir to Alberia.
My name is Jinlorda, but you may\nfeel free to refer to me as Jin.
So the wings on my back would indicate!\n...Ah, right, of course.
I suspect this is your first time seeing\nso large a faerie, yes?
Small wonder, seeing as faeries do not\ntypically reside in South Grastaea.
Among our kind, you likely only know\nyour small friend, Notte.
I do, though the awareness is not mutual.\nI saw her long ago, when she was young.
But faeries as small and weak as her\nare now a bygone relic of the past.
Our kind has been unshackled from\nbodily weakness by the secret art of\nmetamorphosis!
Metamorphosis is a technique which\ndraws on the power of mana in order\nto make faeries larger.
I'd heard tell that faeries naturally took on\nsuch forms at some point in their lives.
Indeed we do. Yet with metamorphosis,\nwe are able to maintain that size.
To be certain, there exist in my kingdom\nhardliners who mislike the technique...
But they are woefully behind the times.\nWe faeries ought to be strong, large,\nand beautiful!

With metamorphosis, we will spread our
great wings, break free from the confines
of our kingdom, and soar toward the wider
world steadfast and true!
Higher in the skies even than the Sacred\nTree does stretch! Beyond the clear blue\nskies and away! Away! AWAY!
The mere thought of such a splendiferous\nspectacle sends a thrill through me!
Forgive me, honored guests; I fear my\neagerness for this day runs unchecked.
And you say I haven't changed...
Disquieting signs from the city, sire:\nThere appear to be individuals taking\nadvantage of the turmoil to act.
Matters grow ever turbulent. To be safe,\nheighten the guard at the royal palace.
Also, command the citizenry to remain\ninside their homes for now.
All shall be as you decree, sire.
It appears, my dear Zethia, that your other\ntwin brother has come to my kingdom.
Mostlike he comes at Finlorda's invitation.
Finlorda was signatory to the treaty,\nwas he not?
Quite astute. I rather suspect he plans\nto let them in on the truth.
Do you mean the truth about my brother?
Oh ho! Based on the look on your faces,\nthe both of you are most curious indeed!
Well, I suppose you have a right to know.
Then I shall elucidate the details\nbefore we ascend the Sacred Tree.\nI trust this is acceptable, Nedrick?
In that case, permit me to spin you a tale\npassed from lip to ear for many years\nwithin my kingdom...
A tale of a foolish faerie, the prince of a\nforeign land...and the child swap that\ncaught them both in its wake!
